<Layout title="Screenwriter Mortgages · FL Feature + TV Staff Writer + Showrunner + Hybrid Writer-Producer-Director + Documentary Qualifying" description="Florida screenwriter (WGA member) mortgage sub-page covering five practice categories: feature screenwriter operating through loan-out S-corp PLLC with spec script sales plus option fees plus rewrite-polish fees; TV staff writer with W-2 from production company at WGA-scale weekly rates across episodic seasons; showrunner / executive producer with W-2 plus creator bonus plus script fees plus residuals plus sometimes back-end participation plus overall deals at studios and streamers; hybrid writer-producer-director with W-2 staff writing plus 1099 directing fees plus S-corp loan-out producing fees; documentary plus non-fiction plus branded content writer with 1099 contract. WGAW Writers Guild of America West. WGAE Writers Guild of America East. WGA Minimum Basic Agreement MBA negotiated every 3 years. 2023 WGA strike outcomes including AI protections plus streaming residual increases plus viewership metric transparency plus minimum staffing requirements. AMPTP Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers. WGA Pension Plan plus Health Fund. WGA Residuals administration. WGA scale minimums (Staff Writer through Supervising Producer levels). Loan-out company S-corp PLLC standard structure. Multi-source mortgage qualifying under Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01 W-2 staff writing with 24-month averaging on season-compressed income. B3-3.2-01 self-employed for 1099 spec sales plus rewrites plus directing fees. B3-3.4-02 partnership / S-corp K-1 for loan-out with multi-entity Form 1084 analysis plus reasonable compensation analysis. Residuals supplementary income. Conventional Conforming. Conventional Jumbo. Bank Statement Non-QM 12-24 months loan-out plus personal bank deposits. P&L Statement Non-QM. Asset-Depletion Non-QM. DSCR Non-QM investor. Cash-Out Refinance. Construction-to-Perm. Streaming era residuals strengthened by 2023 MBA. Florida no state income tax substantial showrunner qualifying advantage." canonical="https://stairwaymortgage.com/creative-earners/screenwriters/">
  <div class="screenwriter-scope" set:html={screenwriterBody} />
</Layout>

